41:06.047 --> 41:07.047
Usual.

41:08.841 --> 41:10.547
Eggs over bacon and grits.

41:12.178 --> 41:13.213
Same.

41:18.184 --> 41:20.140
Bobby: I need two over,
grits, fried.

41:29.821 --> 41:31.221
Wilbur: Wilbur tennant.

41:31.364 --> 41:33.524
Kathleen: He's not in his office.
Can I take a message?

41:36.119 --> 41:38.201
But he really can't get
to the phone right now.

41:38.287 --> 41:39.572
I want service!

41:40.081 --> 41:42.441
I'll let him know that you called again.
For Christ's sakes.

41:44.877 --> 41:47.334
Is she getting accustomed
to being at mom and dad's?

41:47.422 --> 41:49.233
Beth: You know grammer.
She misses her own house.

41:49.257 --> 41:51.669
What? She misses her own house.

41:52.510 --> 41:54.046
I have a bad cell.

41:54.137 --> 41:56.378
I said grammer
misses her own house.

41:56.472 --> 41:57.928
Okay, can you...

41:58.349 --> 41:59.634
Can I talk to her?

41:59.726 --> 42:01.006
She and mom are at the doctor's.

42:01.686 --> 42:04.348
Will you tell grammers I called?
Rob, you're breaking up.

42:04.439 --> 42:05.519
And mom too?

42:05.606 --> 42:07.142
Let's try again on Sunday.
All right.

42:15.950 --> 42:17.190
"C-8."

42:23.458 --> 42:25.790
You know you look like
a crazy person, right?

42:25.877 --> 42:28.243
What was the name of that guy
that you brought by the...

42:28.671 --> 42:32.004
What guy? The chemistry expert.

42:32.091 --> 42:33.877
The guy who does the models.
Gillespie.

42:37.055 --> 42:38.055
Here you go.

42:39.057 --> 42:40.057
Thank you.

42:40.475 --> 42:42.215
Kim Burke
had an expense account.

42:42.852 --> 42:45.138
Oh, sorry. It's not
that kind of case.

42:45.897 --> 42:50.015
Are you familiar
with something called pfoa?

42:51.736 --> 42:52.771
No.

42:55.448 --> 42:56.779
No. No.

42:57.450 --> 43:01.989
I did read something recently
about a pfos, I think it was.

43:02.121 --> 43:05.079
That sounds related.
And what was that?

43:05.708 --> 43:08.666
Long-chain fluorocarbon,
synthetic.

43:09.796 --> 43:13.084
I'm sorry. Chemistry was
my worst class in high school.

43:14.008 --> 43:15.498
Boy, you in the wrong
line of work.

43:15.593 --> 43:17.959
Tell me about it. So?

43:18.387 --> 43:20.844
So, synthetic. All right?
Man-made.

43:21.933 --> 43:23.048
Frankenstein.

43:23.851 --> 43:24.931
And?

43:25.645 --> 43:29.729
Long-chain fluorocarbon is a sequence
of carbon atoms, add a fluoride.

43:30.983 --> 43:34.771
All right. In the lab you take
a carbon atom... mmm-hmm.

43:34.862 --> 43:38.025
And then you add
another carbon atom.

43:38.574 --> 43:39.574
And then another

43:40.409 --> 43:42.024
and another... look.

43:43.621 --> 43:46.363
You're making a chain. Right?

43:49.252 --> 43:51.243
Right? Could it be...

43:52.171 --> 43:54.127
Eight? Eight carbons?

43:54.215 --> 43:56.752
Well, sure. Yeah, in the lab
you can do almost anything.

43:57.468 --> 44:00.676
And why would you want to?
Make this, I mean.

44:02.723 --> 44:06.386
Well, a chain like that's pretty much
unbreakable, biochemically speaking.

44:06.477 --> 44:09.389
So, uh, industrial uses,
I imagine.

44:10.231 --> 44:11.641
3m made it.

44:12.150 --> 44:14.232
They don't anymore.
That's what I read.

44:14.777 --> 44:17.314
Why did they stop? Didn't say.

44:19.782 --> 44:20.782
What if...

44:22.451 --> 44:23.941
What if you drank it?

44:26.581 --> 44:27.581
Drank it?

44:28.583 --> 44:30.244
You don't.
Well, what if you did?

44:30.793 --> 44:32.909
Ready to order? Yeah,
I think I'd like a...

44:34.046 --> 44:35.206
But what if you did?

44:36.549 --> 44:39.086
That's like saying,
"what if I swallowed a tire?"

44:40.720 --> 44:43.132
I don't know. You wanna be
the guy that finds out?

44:44.807 --> 44:45.807
Tuna melt.

45:05.161 --> 45:10.201
Preacher: Let us all begin with hymn
number 452 in our hymnal books.

45:10.291 --> 45:13.249
"Here I am, lord." Please rise.

