does it makes sounds?

45:38.778 --> 45:40.338
Female voice: Asteroid ahead.

45:40.571 --> 45:43.313
You hold like that.

45:43.407 --> 45:45.568
Male voice:
Are you ready to blast off?

45:58.881 --> 46:00.746
Teddy: I'm taking off that.

46:31.622 --> 46:32.987
Rob: You said it had fluoride?

46:33.791 --> 46:35.477
Dr. Gillespie: What?
Mr. bilott, it's Sunday.

46:35.501 --> 46:38.208
That chemical, you said
it had a fluoride atom.

46:39.755 --> 46:42.747
It's a fluorocarbon, so, yes.
Somewhere along the chain...

46:42.842 --> 46:45.208
What would it do to your
teeth if you drank it?

46:45.303 --> 46:47.385
Don't tell me if you
shouldn't, if you did.

46:47.471 --> 46:49.711
If you drank a lot of it, what
would it do to your teeth?

46:50.224 --> 46:52.510
Well, in trace amounts
fluoride hardens teeth.

46:52.601 --> 46:57.311
But too much, it's gonna stain 'em.
I mean, even turn 'em black.

46:58.816 --> 47:00.681
So, can I get back
to my family now?

47:05.323 --> 47:06.563
What? Where are you going?

47:06.991 --> 47:09.528
It's in their water.
What? What is?

47:47.198 --> 47:48.638
Doctor: How long's
the coughing been?

47:50.117 --> 47:52.699
Wilbur: Couple...
Couple of months.

47:53.245 --> 47:54.245
A year.

47:54.705 --> 47:58.323
You a smoker? No.

47:59.085 --> 48:01.005
Roll up your sleeve.
We're gonna take some blood.

48:15.601 --> 48:18.468
Thought you left him inside.
I did.

48:23.150 --> 48:24.390
Oh, baby.

48:34.203 --> 48:35.203
You move this?

